#: ../topics/logging.rst:3
msgid "Logging"
msgstr ""

#: ../topics/logging.rst:4
msgid ""
"IdentityServer uses the standard logging facilities provided by ASP.NET "
"Core. The Microsoft `documentation <https://docs.microsoft.com/en-"
"us/aspnet/core/fundamentals/logging>`_ has a good intro and a description"
" of the built-in logging providers."
msgstr ""

#: ../topics/logging.rst:7
msgid "We are roughly following the Microsoft guidelines for usage of log levels:"
msgstr ""

#: ../topics/logging.rst:9
msgid ""
"``Trace`` For information that is valuable only to a developer "
"troubleshooting an issue. These messages may contain sensitive "
"application data like tokens and should not be enabled in a production "
"environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../topics/logging.rst:10
msgid ""
"``Debug`` For following the internal flow and understanding why certain "
"decisions are made. Has short-term usefulness during development and "
"debugging."
msgstr ""

#: ../topics/logging.rst:11
msgid ""
"``Information`` For tracking the general flow of the application. These "
"logs typically have some long-term value."
msgstr ""

#: ../topics/logging.rst:12
msgid ""
"``Warning`` For abnormal or unexpected events in the application flow. "
"These may include errors or other conditions that do not cause the "
"application to stop, but which may need to be investigated."
msgstr ""

#: ../topics/logging.rst:13
msgid ""
"``Error`` For errors and exceptions that cannot be handled. Examples: "
"failed validation of a protocol request."
msgstr ""

#: ../topics/logging.rst:14
msgid ""
"``Critical`` For failures that require immediate attention. Examples: "
"missing store implementation, invalid key material..."
msgstr ""

